     1→# Parchment & Renaissance Aesthetic - Extracted from Serenissima
     2→
     3→## What It Does
     4→Creates a warm, Renaissance Venice aesthetic using parchment backgrounds, gold accents, and classic serif typography. The system combines:
     5→- **Parchment texture**: SVG noise filter for paper grain
     6→- **Typography**: Cinzel (headers) + Crimson Text (body)
     7→- **Color palette**: Warm parchment (#f5e7c1), gold metallics, Mediterranean blues
     8→- **Visual effects**: Subtle animations, gold shimmer, paper-like textures
     9→
    10→## How It Works
    11→
    12→### Parchment Texture Generation
    13→Uses inline SVG with feTurbulence filter to create realistic paper grain texture as a data URI background image.
    14→
    15→**Technical approach:**
    16→- SVG filter with fractalNoise turbulence
    17→- Base frequency 0.8 with 4 octaves for fine grain
    18→- Stitch tiles to create seamless pattern
    19→- Low opacity (0.08) for subtle effect
    20→- Applied as CSS background-image
    21→
    22→## Original Implementation
    23→
    24→### Parchment Background (from globals.css)
    25→
    26→```css
    27→.bg-parchment {
    28→  background-color: #f5e7c1; /* Warm parchment base color */
    29→  background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width='100' height='100' viewBox='0 0 100 100' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='noise'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.8' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100' height='100' filter='url(%23noise)' opacity='0.08'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
    30→}
    31→```
    32→
    33→**Decoded SVG:**
    34→```xml
    35→<svg width='100' height='100' viewBox='0 0 100 100' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'>
    36→  <filter id='noise'>
    37→    <feTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.8' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/>
    38→  </filter>
    39→  <rect width='100' height='100' filter='url(#noise)' opacity='0.08'/>
    40→</svg>
    41→```
    42→
    43→### Typography System
    44→
    45→```css
    46→@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600;700&family=Crimson+Text:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400;1,600;1,700&display=swap');
    47→
    48→:root {
    49→  --font-header: 'Cinzel', serif;
    50→  --font-body: 'Crimson Text', serif;
    51→}
    52→
    53→body {
    54→  font-family: var(--font-body);
    55→  line-height: 1.5;
    56→}
